Active models refer to models that are currently being used or are in production; 
Recent scores refer to scores created within the last 30 days, indicating the models' current performance;
Average score threshold of 0.5 could be considered as a minimum performance benchmark or a criteria for model evaluation.

* Models are machine learning models;
* The scores are a measure of model performance;
* Comments and ratings are a measure of model engagement;
* Average score, comment count, and average rating are calculated over all model generations.
